text.tspan: Death rates in the United States through the 20th century
The reported annual death rate, based on the underlying cause listed on death certificates. This is shown as a crude
rate per 100,000 people; it does not account for changes in the age structure of the population.
Data source: Centre for Diseases Control (CDC)
Note: Data for specific causes may be missing or transient if they enter or fall out of the top 10 reported causes of deaths in any year.
